{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, when used in conjunction with machine learning-based systems and medical ontologies, they show promising performances.",
    "For example, a rule-based NLP system integrating the Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) and regular expression developed by Shivadda et al.",
    "achieved an F1 score of 90.7 for extracting risk factors of heart diseases.",
    "[15] Roberts et al.",
    "also showed by augmenting the training data with fine-grained annotations and negative examples, a Support Vector Machine (SVM)-based classifier can also achieve a F1 score of 0.9276 on the same task."
  ]
}